OL,3,CBlood test could identify millions of
OL,4,Cpeople spreading tuberculosis
OL,5,Cunknowingly
OL,7,FScientists say they are close to
OL,8,Fdeveloping a blood test that could
OL,9,Fidentify millions of people who spread
OL,10,Ftuberculosis unknowingly.
OL,12,FResearchers from the University of
OL,13,FSouthampton have discovered a group of
OL,14,Fbiological markers that are found in
OL,15,Fhigh levels among infectious patients.
OL,17,FTuberculosis, or TB, is the world's
OL,18,Fdeadliest infectious disease and kills
OL,19,Fmore than one million people each
OL,20,Fyear, according to World Health
OL,21,FOrganisation data.
