OL,3,CBlood test could identify millions of
OL,4,Cpeople spreading tuberculosis
OL,5,Cunknowingly
OL,7,FThe study, carried out with experts
OL,8,Ffrom the University of Cape Town in
OL,9,FSouth Africa and Cayetano Heredia
OL,10,FUniversity in Lima, Peru, used a new
OL,11,Ftechnique that identified a set of six
OL,12,Fproteins that are highly accurate in
OL,13,Fpinpointing TB.
OL,15,FLead author Dr Hannah Schiff, a
OL,16,Frespiratory expert at Southampton,
OL,17,Fsaid if successfully produced, a test
OL,18,Fcould help identify the estimated
OL,19,Fthree million cases which were missed
OL,20,Flast year, mostly in developing
OL,21,Fcountries.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G2/8
