OL,3,CBlood test could identify millions of
OL,4,Cpeople spreading tuberculosis
OL,5,Cunknowingly
OL,7,FStudy co-director Dr Diana Garay-
OL,8,FBaquero, also from Southampton, said
OL,9,Fthe findings were a roadmap to
OL,10,Fdeveloping a TB test that would be as
OL,11,Fsimple as the lateral flows used
OL,12,Fduring the Covid-19 pandemic.
OL,14,FShe said: "The new markers we
OL,15,Fdiscovered are truly exciting but the
OL,16,Fimportant work now is to develop these
OL,17,Finto tests that can be used for the
OL,18,Fmillions of people who are
OL,19,Ftransmitting TB without knowing it.
